headline: F5: Margin Strength Meets Trust Deficit As It Faces Its Biggest Security Test Yet
summary: F5's FY 2025 revenue rose 10% to $3.09 billion, with a non-GAAP gross margin of 83.6% and an operating margin of 37%. Click here to find out why FFIV is a Hold.

headline: F5 (FFIV) Margin Expansion Reinforces Bullish Narratives Despite Slower Forward Growth
summary: F5 (FFIV) reported earnings growth of 22.2% over the past year, outpacing its robust five-year average yearly increase of 19.2%. Net profit margins improved to 22.4% from 20.1% a year ago, while earnings are forecast to grow at 10.01% annually with revenue expected to rise at 3.9% per year. Both figures trail the broader US market’s outlook.
